Cell["\<\
The symbolic form of the matrix occupies approximately 30 \
pages!\
\>", "Text"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Code Generation", "Subsection"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "We need to declare types of the argument and returnvalue of the function \
to be compiled. In this case a list of ",
  "10",
  " real parameters and a real 10",
  StyleBox[" \[Cross] ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  "10 matrix."
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    \(Declare[
      SymbolicMatrix[Real\ x_, Real\ y_, Real\ z_, Real\ u_, Real\ v_, 
          Real\ w_, Real\ a_, Real\ b_, Real\ c_, Real\ d_] \[Rule] 
        Real[10, 10]]\)], "Input"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "We generate C++ code and compile it to an executable file using the ",
  StyleBox["BuildCode",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command. The option ",
  StyleBox["EvaluateFunctions",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " makes optimiizations such as common subexpression eliminations and \
symbolic evaluation of the function ",
  StyleBox["SymbolicMatrix",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " before code generation."
}], "Text"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
    \(BuildCode[EvaluateFunctions \[Rule] {SymbolicMatrix}]\)], "Input"],

Cell[BoxData[
    \("Successful compilation to C++: 1 function(s)"\)], "Print"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
  "Connect the executable to ",
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]
}], "Text"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
    \(\(InstallCode[];\)\)], "Input"],

Cell[BoxData[
    InterpretationBox[\("Global"\[InvisibleSpace]" is installed."\),
      SequenceForm[ "Global", " is installed."],
      Editable->False]], "Print"]
}, Open  ]],

